{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"thread, passing it a [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] which will be run by a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ever call [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"], assuming you want"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the new [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the thread.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"cycle is managed by a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"text":"), it is always suggested to wrap","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] inside a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, otherwise threads that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"] reference they hold.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"asynchronous operation inside a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, but it is up to you to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"started while the non-default context is active."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF","extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"method","title":"pushThreadDefault()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(such as most ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes the context returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"code":"GLib.idle_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol\/pushthreaddefault()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol\/pushThreadDefault()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"../gio/index.html":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Gio","type":"text"}],"title":"Gio","type":"link","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","url":"..\/gio\/index.html"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ThreadPool","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","title":"MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextProtoc